.\" Man page for loofi-fedora-tweaks
.TH LOOFI\-FEDORA\-TWEAKS 1 "2026-02-16" "42.0.0" "Loofi Fedora Tweaks Manual"
.SH NAME
loofi\-fedora\-tweaks \- comprehensive system management for Fedora
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B loofi\-fedora\-tweaks
[\fB\-\-daemon\fR]
[\fB\-\-cli\fR [\fIcommand\fR ...]]
[\fB\-\-web\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B loofi\-fedora\-tweaks
is a PyQt6 desktop application for Fedora 43+ (KDE Plasma) providing
system maintenance, developer tooling, AI integration, security hardening,
window management, virtualization, mesh networking, and workspace state
teleportation.
.PP
When launched without options, the graphical user interface is displayed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-daemon
Run as a background daemon for scheduled tasks.  The daemon is managed
by a systemd user unit (\fBloofi\-fedora\-tweaks.service\fR).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-cli " [" \fIcommand\fR " ...]"
Run in command\-line mode.  Any remaining arguments are forwarded to the
CLI dispatcher (see \fBCLI COMMANDS\fR below).
.TP
.B \-\-web
Run the headless Loofi Web API server (FastAPI/Uvicorn).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version string and exit.
.SH CLI COMMANDS
The following subcommands are available in CLI mode
(\fB\-\-cli\fR):
.TP
.B info
Show system information.
.TP
.B health
System health check overview.
.TP
.B disk \fR[\fB\-\-details\fR]
Display disk usage.  With \fB\-\-details\fR, show large directories.
.TP
.B processes \fR[\fB\-n\fR \fIcount\fR] [\fB\-\-sort\fR \fIcpu\fR|\fImemory\fR]
Show top processes sorted by CPU (default) or memory usage.
.TP
.B temperature
Show hardware temperature readings.
.TP
.B netmon \fR[\fB\-\-connections\fR]
Network interface monitoring.
.TP
.B cleanup \fR[\fIaction\fR] [\fB\-\-days\fR \fIN\fR]
System cleanup.  Actions: \fBall\fR (default), \fBdnf\fR, \fBjournal\fR,
\fBtrim\fR, \fBautoremove\fR, \fBrpmdb\fR.
.TP
.B tweak \fIaction\fR \fR[\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR] [\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR]
Hardware tweaks.  Actions: \fBpower\fR, \fBaudio\fR, \fBbattery\fR, \fBstatus\fR.
.TP
.B advanced \fIaction\fR \fR[\fB\-\-value\fR \fIN\fR]
Advanced optimizations.  Actions: \fBdnf\-tweaks\fR, \fBbbr\fR,
\fBgamemode\fR, \fBswappiness\fR.
.TP
.B network dns \fR[\fB\-\-provider\fR \fIname\fR]
Network configuration.  Providers: \fBcloudflare\fR (default), \fBgoogle\fR,
\fBquad9\fR, \fBopendns\fR.
.TP
.B doctor
Check system dependencies and diagnostics.
.TP
.B hardware
Show detected hardware profile.
.TP
.B plugins \fIaction\fR \fR[\fIname\fR]
Manage plugins.  Actions: \fBlist\fR, \fBenable\fR, \fBdisable\fR.
.TP
.B plugin\-marketplace \fIaction\fR \fR[\fIplugin\fR]
Plugin marketplace operations.  Actions: \fBsearch\fR, \fBinstall\fR,
\fBuninstall\fR, \fBupdate\fR, \fBinfo\fR, \fBlist\-installed\fR.
.TP
.B vm \fIaction\fR \fR[\fIname\fR]
Virtual machine management.  Actions: \fBlist\fR, \fBstatus\fR,
\fBstart\fR, \fBstop\fR.
.TP
.B vfio \fIaction\fR
GPU passthrough assistant.  Actions: \fBcheck\fR, \fBgpus\fR, \fBplan\fR.
.TP
.B mesh \fIaction\fR
Loofi Link mesh networking.  Actions: \fBdiscover\fR, \fBstatus\fR.
.TP
.B support\-bundle
Export a support bundle ZIP for troubleshooting.
.SH GLOBAL CLI FLAGS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output in JSON format for scripting.
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " seconds"
Operation timeout (default: 300).
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show commands without executing them.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/loofi\-fedora\-tweaks/
Application directory containing all Python modules and assets.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/loofi\-fedora\-tweaks/
User data directory (logs, plugins, settings).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/loofi\-fedora\-tweaks/startup.log
Startup and runtime log.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PYTHONPATH
Set automatically by the launcher script to include the application
directory.
.SH SECURITY
All privileged operations use \fBpkexec\fR(1) via polkit policies.  The
application never uses \fBsudo\fR.
